  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do people with very high IQs do all day?",
  "response": "People with very high IQs engage in a wide variety of activities, much like anyone else. Their interests and daily routines can vary greatly depending on their personal preferences, professional responsibilities, and individual circumstances. Here are some common activities that people with very high IQs might engage in:\n\n1. **Professional Work**: Many individuals with high IQs pursue careers that challenge their intellectual abilities, such as in academia, research, technology, engineering, medicine, law, or business. They might spend significant amounts of time working on complex projects, solving problems, or innovating in their fields.\n\n2. **Learning and Education**: Intellectual curiosity often drives people with high IQs to continually seek new knowledge. They might spend time reading books, taking online courses, attending seminars, or engaging in self-study on various topics.\n\n3. **Creative Pursuits**: High IQ individuals may be drawn to creative activities such as writing, art, music, or design. These activities allow them to express their ideas and explore new forms of creativity and problem-solving.\n\n4. **Research and Development**: Conducting research and developing new theories or technologies can be a major focus for some. They might work in academic or corporate research departments, exploring new ideas and advancing knowledge in their fields.\n\n5. **Problem-Solving**: Many high IQ individuals enjoy tackling puzzles, games, and other activities that challenge their cognitive abilities. This could include chess, programming, mathematical problems, or strategic games.\n\n6. **Social and Community Involvement**: Intellectual engagement is not limited to solitary activities. Many high IQ individuals are involved in various social, community, and philanthropic efforts, seeking to make a positive impact on society.\n\n7. **Physical and Recreational Activities**: Like everyone else, people with high IQs also engage in physical activities to maintain their health and well-being. This can include exercise, sports, outdoor activities, and hobbies that provide relaxation and recreation.\n\n8. **Technology and Innovation**: They might stay up-to-date with the latest technological advancements and innovations, exploring new gadgets, software, and scientific developments.\n\nIt's important to note that having a high IQ does not dictate one's interests or daily activities entirely. Personal passions, life circumstances, and opportunities play a significant role in shaping what individuals choose to do with their time.",
